This paper deals with the relationship between logical models and the answers of definite clause programs, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper discusses the use of logical models (specifically, least Herbrand models) in characterizing program answers. The paper also touches on topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), programming languages (cs.PL), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE), as it deals with the semantics of programming languages and the relationship between program behavior and logical models.
